<% content_for :title, "HoneyOps | Cookie Policy" %>
<% content_for :meta_description, "Cookie Policy for HoneyOps describing strictly necessary cookies and browser management options." %>

<div class="min-h-screen bg-slate-950 text-slate-100">
  <%= render "main/site_header" %>

  <main>
    <section class="border-b border-slate-900 bg-slate-950 py-16">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-100 sm:text-5xl">Cookie Policy</h1>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-400">Last updated: March 12, 2026</p>
        <p class="mt-6 text-slate-300">
          This policy explains how HoneyOps uses cookies on honeyops.net and related service domains.
          We use only cookies that are strictly necessary for secure operation of the platform.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-slate-950 py-16">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl space-y-8 px-6 text-slate-300">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">1. What are cookies?</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
            Cookies are small text files stored on your device by websites to maintain state and
            remember information needed for normal functionality.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">2. Cookies we use</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm">HoneyOps uses only essential cookies, including:</p>
          <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-sm">
            <li><span class="font-semibold text-slate-100">Session cookie</span> (for example `_honeyops_session`) to maintain secure login sessions.</li>
            <li><span class="font-semibold text-slate-100">Security cookies</span> used for protection mechanisms such as CSRF mitigation.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">3. Cookies we do not use</h2>
          <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-sm">
            <li>Advertising or marketing cookies.</li>
            <li>Social media tracking pixels.</li>
            <li>Behavioral profiling or fingerprinting techniques.</li>
            <li>Non-essential analytics cookies.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">4. Browser controls</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
            You can block or delete cookies in your browser settings. If essential cookies are disabled,
            parts of the HoneyOps platform may not function correctly, including authentication.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">5. Contact</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
            For any question regarding cookies and privacy,
            contact <a href="mailto:privacy@honeyops.net" class="text-amber-400 hover:underline">privacy@honeyops.net</a>.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm">
            See also our <%= link_to "Privacy Policy", privacy_path, class: "text-amber-400 hover:underline" %>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <%= render "main/site_footer" %>
</div>
